    <h2><a href=3D"https://www.themarthablog.com/2025/12/the-boxwood-allee-=
is-covered-in-burlap.html" rel=3D"bookmark" title=3D"Permanent Link to The =
Boxwood All=C3=A9e is Covered in Burlap">The Boxwood All=C3=A9e is Covered =
in Burlap</a></h2>

    <div class=3D"entry">
      <p>My Boxwood All=C3=A9e is ready for winter.</p>
<p>I've been covering my boxwood specimens with burlap since I first starte=
d to garden. Burlap covers protect the tender branches from splaying and br=
eaking from the weight of snow, while shielding the foliage from freezing w=
indburn. I think it also provides a cozy and pretty look to the winter land=
scape. Yesterday, my outdoor grounds crew enveloped my entire Boxwood All=
=C3=A9e, transforming its appearance for the season.</p>
<p>Enjoy these photos.</p>

	=09
		<div id=3D"gallery-2" class=3D"gallery galleryid-153290 gallery-columns-1=
 gallery-size-medium"><dl class=3D"gallery-item">
			<dt class=3D"gallery-icon portrait">
				<a href=3D"https://static.themarthablog.com/2025/12/PXL_20231208_150048=
536-scaled.jpg" class=3D"cboxElement"><img src=3D"https://www.themarthablog=
.com/wp-content/plugins/lazy-load/images/1x1.trans.gif" data-lazy-src=3D"ht=
tps://static.themarthablog.com/2025/12/PXL_20231208_150048536-264x300.jpg" =
loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"264" height=3D"300" class=3D"a=
ttachment-medium size-medium colorbox-153290 " alt=3D"The burlap gets reuse=
d from year to year whenever possible. When it is removed in spring, it is =
rolled up, labeled and then stored in the dry stable barn until it is used =
